-- Egypt stock exchange to close on Wednesday for national holiday 
-- 
-- Mon Jul 21, 2014 07:13AM EDT
-- None



CAIRO, July 21 (Reuters) - Egypt's stock exchange <.EGX30> will close on July 23 for a national holiday marking the army's ousting of King Farouk in 1952, it said in a statement on Monday.

Trading will resume on Thursday, it said.